<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About – TrailRide Advisor</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark mb-4">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">TrailRide Advisor</a>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarSupportedContent"
        aria-controls="navbarSupportedContent" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarSupportedContent">
        <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto align-items-center">
          <% if (user) { %>
            <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/trails">Trails</a></li>
            <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/logout">Logout</a></li>
          <% } else { %>
            <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/signup">Sign Up</a></li>
            <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/login">Login</a></li>
          <% } %>
          <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/about">About</a></li>
          <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/references">References</a></li>
          <!-- Theme toggle -->
          <li class="nav-item">
            <div class="form-check form-switch mt-2 ms-3">
              <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="theme-toggle">
              <label class="form-check-label text-white" for="theme-toggle">Dark Mode</label>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1>About TrailRide Advisor</h1>
    <section id="mission" class="mb-4">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        TrailRide Advisor is dedicated to connecting mountain bikers to the restorative power of nature by providing comprehensive trail information that enhances physical wellness, mental clarity, and creative inspiration. Our goal is to foster a community of environmentally aware riders who appreciate and respect the landscapes they explore, informed by reliable, real-time data on trail conditions, air quality, and weather.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="story" class="mb-4">
      <h2>My Story</h2>
      <p>
        Ever since I was a kid, mountain biking has been more than just a sport—it's been my sanctuary and my playground. Riding through forests, navigating desert washes, and weaving among cacti doesn't just challenge my physical abilities; it invigorates my mind and allows me space to reflect and recharge. The joy I find in negotiating technical terrain is akin to solving a complex puzzle, each trail a new challenge, each ride a fresh solution. Inspired by my personal connection with Tucson’s trails and my educational experiences in the University of Arizona’s course, "The Great Outdoors: Improving Health, Wellness, and Creativity by Living Life Outside," I set out to create TrailRide Advisor.
      </p>
      <p>
        Like many, I face barriers to engaging with nature—particularly balancing demanding coursework in computer science with the desire to develop this resource. Breaking down the project into manageable milestones has allowed me to progress steadily and turn my vision into reality. My hope is that TrailRide Advisor will help reduce barriers for others, encouraging more people to experience the profound benefits that regular engagement with nature provides.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="course-insights">
      <h2>Connection to Course Insights</h2>
      <p>
        Research consistently demonstrates that engaging with nature significantly enhances our happiness and overall wellness. Florence Williams underscores this in <em>The Nature Fix</em>, emphasizing how nature exposure dramatically elevates mood and well-being compared to urban environments (Williams, 2017). Similarly, Emerson eloquently describes nature’s medicinal quality, its ability to heal and sober the human spirit, asserting that it provides "plain pleasures, kindly and native to us" (Emerson, 1844). Additionally, John Muir celebrates the transformative and sustaining power of America’s forests, highlighting their critical role in nurturing both ecological and human communities (Muir, n.d.).
      </p>
      <p>
        TrailRide Advisor aims to embody these principles by offering detailed trail insights that enable riders to fully immerse themselves in their natural surroundings, benefiting from what Emerson described as nature’s "anciently reported spells" that rejuvenate our minds and bodies (Emerson, 1844).
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
  <!-- Bootstrap JS -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
  <!-- Theme toggle logic -->
  <script>
    (function () {
      const toggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
      const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme');
      const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
      const theme = saved || (prefersDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
      document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', theme);
      if (toggle) toggle.checked = (theme === 'dark');
      toggle.addEventListener('change', function () {
        const t = this.checked ? 'dark' : 'light';
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', t);
        localStorage.setItem('theme', t);
      });
    })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
